#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "Built-in &docker; Orchestration Support"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with &deng; 1.12, container orchestration is now an integral part "
"of the &deng;. Even though this feature is available in &productname;, it is "
"not supported by &suse; and is only provided as a technology preview. Use "
"&k8s; for container orchestration. For details, refer to the <link xlink:"
"href=\"http://kubernetes.io/docs/getting-started-guides/kubeadm/"
"\">Kubernetes documentation</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling the Container Module Using Graphical User Interface &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start &yast;, and select <menuchoice><guimenu>Software</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Software Repositories</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Add</guimenu> to open the add-on dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <guimenu>Extensions and Modules from Registration Server</guimenu> "
"and click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the list of available extensions and modules, select <guimenu>Container "
"Module 15 x86_64</guimenu> and click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The containers module and its repositories will be added to your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use &rmtool;, update the list of repositories on the &rmt; server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling the Container Module from Command Line Using SUSEConnect"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Container Module can be added also with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect -p sle-module-containers/&productnumbershort;/"
"x86_64 -r ''"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "SUSEConnect Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>-r ''</option> flag is required to avoid a known limitation of "
"SUSEConnect."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing and Setting Up the &deng;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install the <systemitem>docker</systemitem> package:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper install docker"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:94
#, no-c-format
msgid "To automatically start the &docker; service at boot time:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl enable docker.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This automatically enables <systemitem>docker.socket</systemitem> in "
"consequence."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use Portus (for more info on Portus, see <xref linkend=\"sec-docker-portus"
"\"/> ) and an SSL-secured registry:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/docker</filename> file. Search for the "
"parameter <parameter>DOCKER_OPTS</parameter> and add <literal>--insecure-"
"registry <replaceable>ADDRESS_OF_YOUR_REGISTRY</replaceable></literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add CA certificates to the directory <filename>/etc/docker/certs.d/"
"<replaceable>REGISTRY_ADDRESS</replaceable></filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;cp CA /etc/pki/trust/anchors/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy the CA certificates to your system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;update-ca-certificates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the &docker; service:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl start docker.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "This automatically starts <systemitem>docker.socket</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &docker; daemon listens on a local socket accessible only by the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user and by the members of "
"the <systemitem class=\"groupname\">docker</systemitem> group. The "
"<systemitem class=\"groupname\">docker</systemitem> group is automatically "
"created during package installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To allow a certain user to connect to the local &docker; daemon, use the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;/usr/sbin/usermod -aG docker <replaceable>USERNAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:159
#, no-c-format
msgid "This allows the user to communicate with the local &docker; daemon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the Network"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To give the containers access the external network, enable the <option>ipv4 "
"ip_forward</option> rule."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "How the &deng; Interacts with <command>iptables</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To learn more about how containers interact with each other and the system "
"firewall, see the <link xlink:href=\"https://docs.docker.com/v17.09/engine/"
"userguide/networking/default_network/container-communication/\">&docker; "
"documentation</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to completely prevent the &deng; from manipulating "
"<command>iptables</command> . See the <link xlink:href=\"https://docs.docker."
"com/network/iptables/#prevent-docker-from-manipulating-iptables\">&docker; "
"documentation</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage Drivers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "&deng; supports different storage drivers:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">vfs</systemitem> : this driver is "
"automatically used when the &docker; host file system does not support copy-"
"on-write. This driver is simpler than the others listed and does not "
"leverage certain advantages of the &deng; such as shared layers. It is a "
"reliable but slow driver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">devicemapper</systemitem> : this driver "
"relies on the device-mapper thin provisioning module. It supports copy-on-"
"write, so it leverages all the advantages of the &deng;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">btrfs</systemitem> : this driver relies on "
"Btrfs to provide all the features required by the &deng;. To use this driver "
"the <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename> directory must be on a Btrfs file "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &productname;&nbsp;12, the Btrfs file system is used by default, which "
"forces the &deng; to use the <systemitem class=\"resource\">btrfs</"
"systemitem> driver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to specify what driver to use by changing the value of the "
"<envar>DOCKER_OPTS</envar> variable defined in the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"docker</filename> file. This can be done either manually or using &yast; by "
"browsing to <menuchoice> <guimenu>System</guimenu> <guimenu>/etc/sysconfig "
"Editor</guimenu> <guimenu>System</guimenu> <guimenu>Management</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>DOCKER_OPTS</guimenu> </menuchoice> menu and entering the "
"<systemitem class=\"library\">-s storage_driver</systemitem> string."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:257
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, to force the usage of the <systemitem class=\"resource"
"\">devicemapper</systemitem> driver enter the following text:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:263
#, no-c-format
msgid "DOCKER_OPTS=\"-s devicemapper\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounting <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is recommended to mount <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename> on a "
"separate partition or volume. In case of file system corruption, this would "
"leave the operating system running the &deng; unaffected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you choose the Btrfs file system for <filename>/var/lib/docker</"
"filename> , it is strongly recommended to create a subvolume for it. This "
"ensures that the directory is excluded from file system snapshots. If you do "
"not exclude <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename> from snapshots, the file "
"system will likely run out of disk space soon after you start deploying "
"containers. In addition, a rollback to a previous snapshot will also reset "
"the &docker; database and images. For more information, see <xref linkend="
"\"sec-snapper-setup-customizing-new-subvolume\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "Updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All updates to the <package>docker</package> package are marked as "
"interactive (that is, no automatic updates) to avoid accidental updates "
"breaking running container workloads. In general, we recommend stopping all "
"running containers before applying an update to &deng;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:295
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid data loss, we do not recommend having workloads rely on containers "
"being startable after an update to &deng;. Although it is technically "
"possible to keep containers running during an update via the <option>--live-"
"restore</option> option, experience has shown that such updates can "
"introduce regressions. &suse; does not support this feature."
msgstr ""
